        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf: isolate doctor core check tests",
        "body": "## Summary\n- isolate doctor core health-check unit tests from real skills/workspace/plugin discovery\n- add an internal health-check dependency seam plus a lazy runtime boundary for real skills readiness detection\n- keep one real e2e smoke proving the missing workspace skill failure and repair path\n\n## Root Cause\n`src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts` looked like a unit test, but several cases executed real doctor checks. That pulled in skills runtime, workspace discovery, plugin skills, and filesystem paths, making the file dominate unit test perf.\n\n## Impact\nThe unit test now covers registry, conversion, scoping, and repair behavior with lightweight fakes. The real filesystem/skills proof remains covered in `doctor-core-checks.e2e.test.ts` outside the unit perf group.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm test src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts -- --reporter=default` -> 6 passed, test time 18ms\n- `pnpm test src/flows/doctor-core-checks.e2e.test.ts -- --reporter=default` -> 1 passed, real skills smoke 523ms\n- `pnpm test src/commands/doctor-skills.test.ts -- --reporter=default` -> 9 passed\n- `pnpm test:perf:imports src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts -- --reporter=default` -> no skills/workspace/plugin-skills chain in top imports\n- `pnpm test:perf:groups` -> `src/flows` 4.8ms; `doctor-core-checks.test.ts` no longer top 25\n- `pnpm check:changed` -> passed\n- `pnpm format:check src/commands/doctor-skills.ts src/commands/doctor-skills-core.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.runtime.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.e2e.test.ts` -> passed\n- `pnpm build` -> passed\n\nNo changelog entry: internal test/perf refactor only.\n",
